AN angry group of community members burnt a ward Councillor's house and car in Goedplaas village outside Modjadjiskloof, in the Tzaneen. It's alleged the accident happened after members of the community went on a rampage. Police spokesperson ColonelÂ  Moatshe Ngoepe said the community members accused their ward Councillor of a variety of issues, they mobilised themselves, attacked her home and then burnt her house with its contents inside. The police were called to the scene, and they arrested eleven suspects. He said the estimated damage caused is more than R400 000. These arrested suspects briefly appeared in the Bolobedu Magistrate's Court on Tuesday for public violence, arson and malicious damage to property. They were all denied bail and their cases were postponed to the 23 May, for a formal bail application. The Provincial Commissioner Lt. General Nneke Ledwaba urged members of the community to follow due processes of the law when they seek to address such issues, without causing any damage to property or harming anyone. Ledwaba said the police will deal with people who commit such acts harshly and without compromise.